# Use VS Code "REST Client" Extension by Huachao Mao to test API endpoints
# Simple alternative to pytest for quick manual testing of specific API endpoints during development

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/prompt-agent

##########################################################################
### Agent prompt endpoint - Add to Cache
# NOTE: Don't add quotes around the instructions_text variables, as they will be included and form invalid JSON
@instructions_text1 = You are a helpful assistant that can write and execute Python code to analyze data and create visualizations.
@instructions_text2 = Always return the code you executed along with the results.
@instructions_text3 = Analyze sales data and create visualizations.

# Pre-requisite: upload a file using the setup API and use the returned file ID in the tool definitions
# Pre-requisite: make sure to use a model deployment that supports code generation (e.g. gpt-4.1) when creating the agent, otherwise the agent will not be able to use the code tool and execute code, and you'll get an error response like: "This model does not support the following tools: CODE"
POST {{baseUrl}}/add-to-cache
Content-Type: application/json  

{
    "agent_name": "code-tool-agent",
    "model_deployment_name": "gpt-4.1",
    "instructions_text": "{{instructions_text1}} {{instructions_text2}} {{instructions_text3}}",
    "tool_definitions": {
        "CODE": {"uploaded_file_id": "assistant-26zUX86n4sb7SkiFYSx9FE"}
    },
    "input_text": "<placeholder>"
}

# Sample response:
#{
#  "status": "created",
#  "chat_conversation_id": "conv_2f90d7325658adee00KNRSzV9ecieC5gmbzwBOcNDEWd6Ai1Pf"
#}

### Agent prompt endpoint - Use the code tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/prompt
Content-Type: application/json  

{
    "chat_conversation_id": "conv_2f90d7325658adee00KNRSzV9ecieC5gmbzwBOcNDEWd6Ai1Pf",
    "agent_name": "code-tool-agent",
    "model_deployment_name": "gpt-4.1",
    "instructions_text": "<placeholder-same-as-before>",
    "input_text": "Calculate the total revenue (price * quantity) for each drink and create a horizontal bar chart showing total revenue by drink, sorted from highest to lowest."
}

